{
  "answer": "The matlaʿ (opening couplet) of the ghazal is:\n\n> آئینہ دیکھ اپنا سا منہ لے کے رہ گئے  \n> صاحب کو دل نہ دینے پہ کتنا غرور تھا[^1]\n\n**Transliteration:**  \n> Aaina dekh apna sa munh le ke reh gaye  \n> Sahab ko dil na dene pe kitna ghuroor tha[^2]\n\n**Translation:**  \n> He saw his face, and all his boasting died;  \n> How great the foolish pride he held inside was.[^3]\n\n[^1]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, ch. 4 (“Aaina dekh apna sa munh le ke reh gaye”), [p-bcbed3](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/04-aaina-dekh-apna-sa-munh-le-ke-reh-gaye/original/#p-bcbed3).\n\n[^2]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, ch. 4 (“Aaina dekh apna sa munh le ke reh gaye”), [p-ee456f](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/04-aaina-dekh-apna-sa-munh-le-ke-reh-gaye/transliteration/#p-ee456f).\n\n[^3]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, ch. 4 (“Aaina dekh apna sa munh le ke reh gaye”), [p-354db2](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/04-aaina-dekh-apna-sa-munh-le-ke-reh-gaye/translation/#p-354db2).",
